    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-02-16</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-03-16T19:53:10Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Provides that, in the case of a member of the Armed Forces who dies while serving on active duty or inactive duty for training, and who dies without a surviving spouse but with one or more children under age 18 who will be in the custody of a parent, brother, or sister, the death gratuity for such member shall be payable to such parent, brother, or sister as designated by the member.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>A bill to amend section 1477 of title 10, United States Code, to provide for the payment of the death gratuity with respect to members of the Armed Forces without a surviving spouse who are survived by a minor child.</title>
